A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Boating – Migratory Waterfowl Season – Prohibited Acts
3 FOR the purpose of prohibiting a person from operating a vessel within a certain distance
4 of a stationary blind or blind site that is occupied and being used for hunting
5 migratory waterfowl during open season; and generally relating to prohibited acts
6 related to boating.
7 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
8 Article – Natural Resources
9 Section 4–512 and 8–701(a) and (s)
10 Annotated Code of Maryland
11 (2023 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
12 BY adding to
13 Article – Natural Resources
14 Section 8–724.2
15 Annotated Code of Maryland
16 (2023 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
17 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
18 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
19 Article – Natural Resources
20 4–512.
21 During the open season for migratory waterfowl, a person may not fish by any means
22 within 500 yards of any stationary blind or blind site which is occupied and is being used
23 for hunting migratory waterfowl.
24 8–701.
