2 SENATE BILL 870
1 (a) In this subtitle the following words have the meanings indicated.
2 (s) (1) “Vessel” means every description of watercraft, including an ice boat
3 but not including a seaplane, that is used or capable of being used as a means of
4 transportation on water or ice.
5 (2) “Vessel” includes the motor, spars, sails, and accessories of a vessel.
6 8–724.2.
7 DURING THE OPEN SEASON FOR MIGRATORY WATERFOWL, A PERSON MAY NOT
8 OPERATE A VESSEL, INCLUDING A KAYAK OR A PADDLE BOAT, IN ANY MANNER
9 WITHIN 500 YARDS OF ANY STATIONARY BLIND OR BLIND SITE THAT IS OCCUPIED
10 AND BEING USED FOR HUNTING MIGRATORY WATERFOWL.
11 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
12 1, 2025.

